ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: The list of values for value types of data and conditions.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The type of an expression with two possible values, "true" and "false". Also, a variable of Boolean type or a function with Boolean arguments or result. The most common Boolean functions are AND, OR and NOT. (http://foldoc.doc.ic.ac.uk/foldoc/foldoc.cgi?Boolean)

Concepts.definition: The type of an expression with two possible values, "true" and "false".

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The sum of a set of values divided by the number of values in the set.

Concepts.definition: The sum of a set of values divided by the number of values in the set.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The value which has an equal number of values greater and less than it.

Concepts.definition: The value which has an equal number of values greater and less than it.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The value which occurs most often in a set of values. If no value is repeated, there is no mode. If more than one value occurs with the same greatest frequency, each value is a mode.

Concepts.definition: The value which occurs most often in a set of values. If no value is repeated, there is no mode. If more than one value occurs with the same greatest frequency, each value is a mode.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Ascertained or determined through monitoring or observation.

Concepts.definition: Ascertained or determined through monitoring or observation.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A statistical measure of the magnitude of a set of variable values. The root mean square is the square root of the mean value for the squares of the original values.

Concepts.definition: A statistical measure of the magnitude of a set of variable values. The root mean square is the square root of the mean value for the squares of the original values.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A measure of the range of values in a set of numbers. Standard deviation is a statistic used as a measure of the dispersion or variation in a distribution, equal to the square root of the arithmetic mean of the squares of the deviations from the arithmetic mean.

Concepts.definition: A measure of the range of values in a set of numbers. Standard deviation is a statistic used as a measure of the dispersion or variation in a distribution, equal to the square root of the arithmetic mean of the squares of the deviations from the arithmetic mean.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A parameter used for calculations involving mechanical properties. The parameter is measured by using dynamic light scattering to obtain the intensity weighted mean hydrodynamic size of a collection of particles.

Concepts.definition: A parameter used for calculations involving mechanical properties. The parameter is measured by using dynamic light scattering to obtain the intensity weighted mean hydrodynamic size of a collection of particles.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Indicates how far and in what direction an item deviates from its distribution's mean, expressed in units of its distribution's standard deviation.

Concepts.definition: A method for converting an individual score into a standard form. The z-score indicates how far and in what direction an item deviates from its distribution's mean, expressed in units of standard deviation. Calculation of a z-score requires knowledge about the population's standard deviation and mean.

ConceptualDomain.preferredDefinition: An organizational header for concepts representing mostly abstract entities.

RepresentationTerm.preferredDefinition: Type; a subdivision of a particular kind of thing.

Concepts.definition: Something distinguishable as an identifiable class based on common qualities.
